@chapter Quartz device

The @code{quartz()} device is the native graphic device in R for Mac OS
X. Its name derives from Apple's Quartz Technology which is essentially
similar to PDF rendering. 

@c One of the most amazing features of Quartz is
@c anti-aliasing which gives you @emph{very nice} plots and images
@c (although the other standard screen devices for @R{} have also supported
@c anti-aliasing for several years).  From its PDF nature it is also
@c resolution independent.

The @code{quartz()} device can be used from @Rapp{} or a suitable build of @R{}
running at the Mac console.  Where supported it is the default graphics
device.

 
